# Testing Standards

## Requirements
- Use Vitest for unit and integration tests
- Use Playwright for E2E tests
- Every public function must have at least one test
- Test files live next to source: `user.service.ts` → `user.service.test.ts`
- Use `describe` blocks grouped by method/function name
- Use `it` with behavior-driven descriptions: `it('should return 404 when user not found')`

## Test Structure (AAA Pattern)

<example>
describe('UserService', () => {
  describe('findById', () => {
    it('should return user when valid ID provided', () => {
      // Arrange
      const mockRepo = createMockRepo({ users: [testUser] });
      const service = new UserService(mockRepo);

      // Act
      const result = service.findById(testUser.id);

      // Assert
      expect(result).toEqual({ ok: true, value: testUser });
    });

    it('should return error when user not found', () => {
      // Arrange
      const mockRepo = createMockRepo({ users: [] });
      const service = new UserService(mockRepo);

      // Act
      const result = service.findById('nonexistent-id');

      // Assert
      expect(result).toEqual({ ok: false, error: expect.any(NotFoundError) });
    });
  });
});
</example>

<example type="invalid">
// ❌ Wrong: no describe grouping, vague name, no AAA
test('user test', () => {
  const result = getUser('123');
  expect(result).toBeTruthy();
});
</example>

## Coverage
- Minimum 80% line coverage for new code
- Critical paths (auth, payments, data processing) require 95%+
- Run `vitest --coverage` before every PR
